PASSENGER INFORMATION
1. Children
are carried free of chaota ge notice in parate santd
on Flights
671/2 and
911/12.
On all other routes, children under two years of age will be
charged at 1/10th of the published adult fare but they shall
not occupy separate seats.
Children who have reached their second birthday but have
not yet reached twelfth will be charged 50% of the publish-
ed adult fare.
2. Free Baggage Allowance
Free baggage allowance for each adult or half-fare passenger
on all international flights shall be limited to 66 pounds (30
kilograms); on all domestic flights inside China, 33 pounds
(15 kilograms).
For children under two years of age, there
is no free baggage allowance.
A passenger may also
sonally carry free of charge unchecked hand baggage of not
more than three kilograms.
3.
Excess Baggage
Excess baggage will be accepted for shipment subject to load
and space available.
Excess baggage charges are assesed at
the rate of one per cent of the published adult fare per
4.
kilogram.
Reservations
Reservations on all CNAC and connecting services can be
made at any CNAC Office.
Hotel accommodation and ground
transportation at destination can be arranged upon request
prior to departure.
5.
Canceilations
CNAC will not guarantee any refund for a cancellation or de-
ferment at short notice.
Passengers are therefore requested
to notify us at the earliest moment if any cancellation or de-
ferment is unavoidable.
6.
Stop-overs
Passengers may break their journey at one or more places en
route with the benefit of the through fare, provided arrange-
ments are made at the time of reservation.
Expenses at such
stop-overs, however, will be for the passenger's account.
7.
Documentation
Passengers must possess all documents such as passports,
visa and health certificates, as may be
required by the laws
of the countries into or over which they are to fly.

any discrepancy in this regard,

Pets

properly caged with good

9.
Arms and Ammunition
Passengers carrying ammunition and/or any kind of weapons
must surrender them to the CNAC
ground staff before em-
barkation.
The CNAC ground staff will, in turn, hand over
same to the captain of the aircraft for safekeeping during the
flight.
